org.eclipse.papyrus.sysml14.constraintblocks

Interface ConstraintBlock

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Block, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstraintBlockCustomImpl, ConstraintBlockImpl

    public interface ConstraintBlock
extends Block
    A representation of the model object 'Constraint Block'. A constraint block is a block that packages the statement of a constraint so it may be applied in a reusable way to constrain properties of other blocks. A constraint block typically defines one or more constraint parameters, which are bound to properties of other blocks in a surrounding context where the constraint is used. Binding connectors, as defined in Chapter 8: Blocks, are used to bind each parameter of the constraint block to a property in the surrounding context. All properties of a constraint block are constraint parameters, with the exception of constraint properties that hold internally nested usages of other constraint blocks.
    See Also:
    ConstraintblocksPackage.getConstraintBlock()
